               <p>THOMAS ELY. On the afternoon of the 17th of July, I was in <placeName id="t18340904-61-crimeloc342">Upper Thames-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-61-crimeloc342" type="placeName" value="Upper Thames-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340904-61-crimeloc342" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340904-61-off340 t18340904-61-crimeloc342"></join> - I felt a tug at my coat, turned round, and saw my handkerchief in the prisoner's hand - he was putting it under his black apron - he was within reach of me - I collared him and gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183409040043"></xptr>
            
