                  </persName>
            . I am an officer - I produce the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>THOMAS ELY. It is my handkerchief.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was walking down Thames-street - I saw some boys throw down the handkerchief - I took it up, and gave it to the gentleman who has claimed it.</p>
               <p>THOMAS ELY. There was nobody so near as the prisoner to me - I felt my coat touched, and turned round.</p>
